      "contents": [
        {
          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"adaptation_kind\":\"Restructure\",\"safety_tier\":\"Green\",\"nudge_patch\":null,\"restructure_plan\":{\"revised_weekly_targets\":[{\"week_number\":1,\"weekly_target_km\":46},{\"week_number\":2,\"weekly_target_km\":52},{\"week_number\":3,\"weekly_target_km\":58}],\"revised_current_week_workouts\":[{\"day_of_week\":2,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":10,\"target_duration_minutes\":60,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Walk or very gentle jog to settle in.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":50,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Hold a fully conversational effort throughout. No tempo creep today.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Slow to a walk for the final few minutes.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"5 minutes of easy walking or very light jogging before settling into your aerobic pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Ease off to a walk for the last few minutes and do a brief stretch of calves and hip flexors.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"This run is unchanged and serves as your aerobic foundation for the week. Keep it genuinely easy — if in doubt, slow down a touch. The goal is blood flow and consistency, not fitness stress.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Recovery-Paced Easy Run\",\"target_distance_km\":8,\"target_duration_minutes\":50,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":370,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":370,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":380,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Very easy start, keep heart rate low.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":40,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Comfortable, controlled effort. You might find a slightly slower pace than normal feels right today — that is perfectly fine.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":385,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Gentle finish, transition to walk.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Start very gently with 5 minutes of easy movement before settling into your aerobic pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk for 2-3 minutes after finishing and stretch your quads and calves.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Thursday's prescribed Tempo session is replaced this week with a shorter, easy-paced run. The priority is restoring freshness, not accumulating threshold stress. Flat legs need easy miles, not hard ones.\",\"perceived_effort\":4},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"title\":\"Short Easy Aerobic Run\",\"target_distance_km\":12,\"target_duration_minutes\":72,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":360,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":360,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Easy walking start to open up the legs.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":62,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":360,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Relaxed aerobic effort. Keep it in the lower end of your easy zone throughout.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":5,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":375,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Slow the last few minutes and walk to finish.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"5 minutes of walking and easy jogging before settling into your easy pace.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk for 2-3 minutes and do a light full-body stretch focusing on legs.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"Saturday's interval session is replaced with a moderate easy run. After three sessions of accumulated fatigue, adding interval stress now would likely deepen the hole rather than build fitness. A steady aerobic run at controlled effort is the smarter investment.\",\"perceived_effort\":5},{\"day_of_week\":0,\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"title\":\"Moderate Long Run\",\"target_distance_km\":16,\"target_duration_minutes\":96,\"target_pace_easy_sec_per_km\":355,\"target_pace_fast_sec_per_km\":355,\"segments\":[{\"segment_type\":\"Warmup\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":365,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Begin at the slower end of easy, let the body settle in.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Work\",\"duration_minutes\":80,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":355,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Steady aerobic long run pace throughout. No progression today — just consistent, controlled effort.\"},{\"segment_type\":\"Cooldown\",\"duration_minutes\":8,\"target_pace_sec_per_km\":370,\"intensity\":\"Easy\",\"repetitions\":1,\"notes\":\"Ease down in the final 8 minutes, walk the last 2.\"}],\"warmup_notes\":\"Start at an easy conversational pace for the first 8-10 minutes before settling into long run effort.\",\"cooldown_notes\":\"Walk for 3-5 minutes after finishing and prioritise hydration, a light snack, and a gentle stretch of the major leg groups.\",\"coaching_notes\":\"The long run is reduced from 22 km to 16 km this week. This isn't a step back in ambition — it's the right stimulus given recent fatigue signals. A 16 km long run at controlled effort will contribute meaningfully to your marathon base without digging the fatigue hole deeper.\",\"perceived_effort\":6}],\"forward_path\":\"Week 2 steps back up to 52 km — roughly a 13% increase from this week's 46 km — with the Tempo session reinstated at full prescribed load and the Saturday intervals returning but at a reduced rep count (4 of 6) to rebuild confidence and sharpness before moving to full volume. Week 3 targets 58 km, reintroducing the full interval set and bringing the long run back toward 20 km. If Week 2 feels smooth and the quality sessions hit their Daniels-Gilbert zones without strain, Week 3 can step closer to the original 68 km target; if there is any residual heaviness, the Week 3 target can hold at 58 km for an extra consolidation week before resuming the original progression toward your sub-3:15 goal.\"},\"net_load_delta\":-16,\"rationale\":\"Shutting down after three reps on Saturday when your legs felt flat and heavy was exactly the right call — pushing through a session your body is clearly not ready for doesn't build fitness, it just extends the time before you can train well again. Looking at the last three sessions together, there is a clear pattern of accumulated fatigue: Thursday's tempo effort was significantly slower than your prescribed threshold band, Saturday's intervals couldn't hold goal pace at all past three reps, and Sunday's long run was cut well short. That isn't a motivation issue — it's your body signalling it needs recovery before it can absorb more training stress. Here is what I've changed this week: Thursday's Tempo is replaced with a shorter, easy-paced 8 km run; Saturday's intervals become a straightforward 12 km easy run; and Sunday's long run is pulled back to 16 km at your normal long-run pace. Tuesday's easy run stays as planned. That brings the week to 46 km — a meaningful step back that gives your legs the space to actually recover. From here, Week 2 steps back up to 52 km with the Tempo session returning at full load and intervals coming back at a reduced rep count so you can rebuild sharpness with confidence. Week 3 targets 58 km with full interval volume and a long run approaching 20 km. One recovery week now protects many weeks of quality training ahead — you're investing in the consistency that sub-3:15 is built on.\",\"referral_category\":null}"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
